Poply SMS/MMS Terms & Conditions
Program Description: When opted-in, you will receive text messages (SMS/MMS) to your mobile number. These messages may include links to Poply invitations and various notifications about these invitations including, but not limited to: notices of messages sent by event hosts, RSVP reminders, and event reminders.
Frequency: Message frequency will vary depending on the specifics of the event. Most guests receive between 4-7 SMS/MMS messages per event.
Opt-in: Hosts are solely responsible for obtaining permission to send invitations to guests via SMS. Unsolicited SMS invitations to guests are expressly prohibited and may result in account termination.
Opt-out: You can cancel the SMS service at any time. Reply to any SMS/MMS message sent by Poply with the keyword ‘STOP’. After you send the SMS message ‘STOP’ to us, we will send you an SMS message to confirm that you have been unsubscribed. After this, you will no longer receive SMS/MMS messages from us. If you want to join again, reply to any SMS/MMS message sent by Poply with the keyword ‘START’ or ‘UNSTOP’.
Help: If you are experiencing issues with the messaging program you can reply with the keyword ‘HELP’ for more assistance, or you can get help directly by emailing cheers@poply.com.
Interruption: Neither Poply nor our partner carriers are liable for delayed or undelivered messages.Hosts are solely responsible for ensuring the accuracy of guest information, including mobile numbers and emails. Poply is not liable for undelivered invitations, invitations sent to unintended recipients, or any issues arising from incorrect information provided by the host.
Cost: Message and data rates may apply for any messages sent to you from us and to us from you. If you have any questions about your text plan or data plan, it is best to contact your wireless provider.
Privacy: If you have any questions regarding privacy, please read our privacy policy above.
